                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 15: The six core infrastructure industries grew 5.6 per cent in fiscal 2007-08 compared with 9.2 per cent in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. However, these key sectors witnessed a growth rate of 9.6 per cent in March compared with an overall industrial growth of 3 per cent during that month. Growth in these core sectors have been fuelled by steel and cement.                            
	 Mumbai, May 15: Telelcom service provider OnMobile Global has signed an agreement to acquire France-based Telisma for an undisclosed amount. Shares of the firm closed at Rs 636, down 1.65 per cent, on the Bombay Stock Exchange.                            
	 Mumbai, May 15: The RBI has relaxed the risk provisioning norm for housing loans up to Rs 30 lakh. The move will make it easier for banks to provide loans for buying residential properties.                            
	 Mumbai, May 15: The Securities Appellate Tribunal has reversed Sebis order in the Goldman Sachs offshore derivatives case. Sebi had imposed a Rs 1-crore penalty on Goldman for not submitting information about the issuance of these instruments in the prescribed format.                             
	 New Delhi, May 15: The government has turned down NTPCs proposal to raise Rs 6,000 crore through a follow-on public offering.                                                                                                                         
